David Potchen, 53, robbed a bank in Merrillville, Indiana, last June and waited for police to arrive so he could go back to prison .
He had lost his job, lost his place to stay and spent a night in the woods before deciding to rob a local Chase bank .
After stealing roughly $1,000 with a note on the back of his resume, he decided to rob another bank so that he could get back in custody .
Potchen had been making $8.29 an hour in prison but had trouble finding a job on his release .